POLICE have discovered another body at a bus accident scene. This after the deaths of 21 people in a head-on crash between a cash-in-transit vehicle and a bus. This brings the total number of fatalities to 22. According to the Limpopo transport and community safety spokeswoman Tidimalo Chuene, a family came forward to report a family member who had been on the bus and was unreachable. REGISTER TO COMMENT! “A family came forward reporting that they could not locate a loved one who was on the bus that plunged into the Phandanama River along the N1 near Hendrik Verwoerd tunnel, after a head-on collision with a cash-in-transit van. “Police divers went back to the culpable homicide scene this morning, 16 February,” she said. Divers then recovered the missing family member.